I think the Russian solution is the best.

They dump high level liquid waste in the deep cold salty waters of the 
arctic ocean.  This water slowly settles, and it will be a thousand or so 
years before it rises again.  In the course of that thousand years, all the 
non actinide radioactives will have decayed, and the most of the actinide 
radioactives will have settled into the mud, and what remains is diluted 
into an enormous volume of water.

     --digsig
